    "tha-ap401:14.2_0": "I offered to peace.",
    "tha-ap401:14.3_0": "lack of dance, a bench,",
    "tha-ap401:14.4_0": "were the supreme among men.",
    "tha-ap401:15.1_0": "it went up to the thighs,",
    "tha-ap401:15.2_0": "while stilling.",
    "tha-ap401:15.3_0": "sown in the seeds,",
    "tha-ap401:15.4_0": "or the sarong of monks.",
    "tha-ap401:16.1_0": "But when lavish food and drink",
    "tha-ap401:16.2_0": "for the mendicant Saṅgha,",
    "tha-ap401:16.3_0": "Telled in a pair,",
    "tha-ap401:16.4_0": "mendicant Saṅgha of mendicants.",
    "tha-ap401:17.1_0": "the wise say,",
    "tha-ap401:17.2_0": "they live with the world again.",
    "tha-ap401:17.3_0": "But the Saṅgha of monks,",
